OL,3,CWe go inside the Severn Tunnel as it
OL,4,Ccloses for major renewal work
OL,6,FTravelling through the Severn Tunnel
OL,7,Fis something many of us are used to.
OL,9,FBut today we're experiencing it in a
OL,10,Fvery different way - journeying on
OL,11,Ffoot to see construction work up close.
OL,13,FThe tunnel is closed from July 3 to
OL,14,FJuly 19 so engineers can replace more
OL,15,Fthan 7km of track.
OL,17,FIt's a mammoth task, with teams also
OL,18,Finstalling more than 10,000 sleepers
OL,19,Fand over 22,000 tonnes of ballast.
