OL,3,CWe go inside the Severn Tunnel as it
OL,4,Ccloses for major renewal work
OL,6,FAs we reach the deepest point of the
OL,7,Ftunnel, Programme Director Ross
OL,8,FMahoney explains the exceptional
OL,9,Fchallenges the team have to deal with.
OL,11,F"There are particular conditions that
OL,12,Fthis railway is exposed to that we
OL,13,Fdon't see anywhere else on the network.
OL,15,F"We see higher levels of rail
OL,16,Fcorrosion due to the salt content of
OL,17,Fthe air. Despite this tunnel lining
OL,18,Fbeing ten bricks deep in places we
OL,19,Fstill see sea water seepage into here."
